    <p> When we got up in the morning the sky was still gray and in the distance we could see a light shower. Nevertheless, we had a lot going on today. </p>
    <p> So we got ready and finally wanted to go to the beach. Clouds or not. After all, we drove here, including the endless sandy beaches and desert -like dunes. Once on the beach, the sun was slowly crawling out. We already had pleasant temperatures. Since the sand was still cold and damp, we decided to go along the beach a little and keep our feet into the water. </p>
    <p> It was wonderful. On the left endless water with good waves to surf. Endless beach and dunes and not a human soul in front of us. God was relaxing. At some point we found that we forgot to smear ourselves with sunscreen and that the sun still has some strength because we started running red. </p>
